018package org.opt4j.benchmarks.dtlz;
019
020import static org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Citation.PublicationMonth.MAY;
021
022import org.opt4j.benchmarks.BinaryCreator;
023import org.opt4j.benchmarks.BinaryToDoubleDecoder;
024import org.opt4j.benchmarks.Bits;
025import org.opt4j.benchmarks.DoubleCopyDecoder;
026import org.opt4j.benchmarks.DoubleCreator;
027import org.opt4j.benchmarks.M;
028import org.opt4j.benchmarks.N;
029import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Citation;
030import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Info;
031import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Order;
032import org.opt4j.core.config.annotations.Required;
033import org.opt4j.core.problem.Creator;
034import org.opt4j.core.problem.Decoder;
035import org.opt4j.core.problem.Evaluator;
036import org.opt4j.core.problem.ProblemModule;
037import org.opt4j.core.start.Constant;
038
039/**
040 * Module for the DTLZ benchmarks as proposed in Deb et al. 2002.
041 * 
042 * @author lukasiewycz
043 * 
044 */
045@Info("DTLZ Problem Suite.  (n = m + k - 1)")
046@Citation(title = "Scalable multi-objective optimization test problems", authors = "Kalyanmoy Deb, Lothar Thiele, Marco Laumanns, and Eckart Zitzler", journal = "Proceedings of the 2002 Congress on Evolutionary Computation", volume = 1, month = MAY, year = 2002, doi = "10.1109/CEC.2002.1007032")
047public class DTLZModule extends ProblemModule {
048
049        @Order(0)
050        @Info("The DTLZ function")
051        protected Function function = Function.DTLZ1;
052
053        @Required(property = "function", elements = { "DTLZ4" })
054        @Order(1)
055        @Constant(value = "alpha", namespace = DTLZ4.class)
056        protected double alpha = 100.0;
057
058        @Order(2)
059        @Info("The number of objectives.")
060        protected int m = 3;
061
062        @Order(3)
063        @Info("The size of the search space.")
064        protected int n = 7;
065
066        @Order(4)
067        @Info("The k value.")
068        protected int k = 5;
069
070        @Order(10)
071        @Info("The encoding of the optimization problem.")
072        protected Encoding encoding = Encoding.DOUBLE;
073
074        @Required(property = "encoding", elements = { "BINARY" })
075        @Info("The number of bits per double value.")
076        protected int bits = 30;
077
078        /**
079         * The used DTZL1 function.
080         * 
081         * @author lukasiewycz
082         */
083        public enum Function {
084                /**
085                 * Use the DTZL1 function.
086                 */
087                DTLZ1,
088                /**
089                 * Use the DTZL2 function.
090                 */
091                DTLZ2,
092                /**
093                 * Use the DTZL3 function.
094                 */
095                DTLZ3,
096                /**
097                 * Use the DTZL4 function.
098                 */
099                DTLZ4,
100                /**
101                 * Use the DTZL5 function.
102                 */
103                DTLZ5,
104                /**
105                 * Use the DTZL6 function.
106                 */
107                DTLZ6,
108                /**
109                 * Use the DTZL7 function.
110                 */
111                DTLZ7;
112        }
113
114        /**
115         * The used encoding type.
116         * 
117         * @author lukasiewycz
118         */
119        public enum Encoding {
120                /**
121                 * Use double values.
122                 */
123                DOUBLE,
124                /**
125                 * Use binary values.
126                 */
127                BINARY;
128        }
129
130        /**
131         * Returns the number of bits per double value.
132         * 
133         * @return the bits
134         */
135        public int getBits() {
136                return bits;
137        }
138
139        /**
140         * Sets the number of bits per double value.
141         * 
142         * @param bits
143         *            the bits to set
144         */
145        public void setBits(int bits) {
146                this.bits = bits;
147        }
148
149        /**
150         * Returns the encoding (double or binary).
151         * 
152         * @return the encoding
153         */
154        public Encoding getEncoding() {
155                return encoding;
156        }
157
158        /**
159         * Set the encoding (double or binary).
160         * 
161         * @param encoding
162         *            the encoding
163         */
164        public void setEncoding(Encoding encoding) {
165                this.encoding = encoding;
166        }
167
168        /**
169         * Returns the DTZL function.
170         * 
171         * @return the DTZL function
172         */
173        public Function getFunction() {
174                return function;
175        }
176
177        /**
178         * Sets the ZDT function.
179         * 
180         * @param function
181         *            the ZDT function
182         */
183        public void setFunction(Function function) {
184                this.function = function;
185
186                switch (function) {
187                default: // DTLZ1
188                        n = 7;
189                        m = 3;
190                        k = 5;
191                        break;
192                case DTLZ2:
193                case DTLZ3:
194                case DTLZ4:
195                case DTLZ5:
196                case DTLZ6:
197                        n = 12;
198                        m = 3;
199                        k = 10;
200                        break;
201                case DTLZ7:
202                        n = 22;
203                        m = 3;
204                        k = 20;
205                        break;
206                }
207
208        }
209
210        /**
211         * Returns the n value.
212         * 
213         * @return the n value
214         */
215        public int getN() {
216                return n;
217        }
218
219        /**
220         * Sets the n value.
221         * 
222         * @param n
223         *            the n value
224         */
225        public void setN(int n) {
226                this.n = n;
227                this.k = n - m + 1;
228        }
229
230        /**
231         * Returns the m value.
232         * 
233         * @return the m
234         */
235        public int getM() {
236                return m;
237        }
238
239        /**
240         * Sets the m value.
241         * 
242         * @param m
243         *            the m to set
244         */
245        public void setM(int m) {
246                this.m = m;
247                this.k = n - m + 1;
248        }
249
250        /**
251         * Returns the k value.
252         * 
253         * @return the k
254         */
255        public int getK() {
256                return k;
257        }
258
259        /**
260         * Sets the k value.
261         * 
262         * @param k
263         *            the k to set
264         */
265        public void setK(int k) {
266                this.k = k;
267                this.n = m + k - 1;
268        }
269
270        /**
271         * Returns the alpha.
272         * 
273         * @return the alpha
274         */
275        public double getAlpha() {
276                return alpha;
277        }
278
279        /**
280         * Sets the alpha.
281         * 
282         * @param alpha
283         *            the alpha to set
284         */
285        public void setAlpha(double alpha) {
286                this.alpha = alpha;
287        }
288
289        /*
290         * (non-Javadoc)
291         * 
292         * @see org.opt4j.start.Opt4JModule#config()
293         */
294        @Override
295        public void config() {
296                n = m + k - 1;
297
298                Class<? extends Creator<?>> creator = null;
299                Class<? extends Decoder<?, ?>> decoder = null;
300                Class<? extends Evaluator<?>> evaluator = null;
301
302                switch (encoding) {
303                case BINARY:
304                        creator = BinaryCreator.class;
305                        decoder = BinaryToDoubleDecoder.class;
306                        break;
307                default: // DOUBLE
308                        creator = DoubleCreator.class;
309                        decoder = DoubleCopyDecoder.class;
310                        break;
311                }
312
313                switch (function) {
314                case DTLZ1:
315                        evaluator = DTLZ1.class;
316                        break;
317                case DTLZ2:
318                        evaluator = DTLZ2.class;
319                        break;
320                case DTLZ3:
321                        evaluator = DTLZ3.class;
322                        break;
323                case DTLZ4:
324                        evaluator = DTLZ4.class;
325                        break;
326                case DTLZ5:
327                        evaluator = DTLZ5.class;
328                        break;
329                case DTLZ6:
330                        evaluator = DTLZ6.class;
331                        break;
332                case DTLZ7:
333                        evaluator = DTLZ7.class;
334                        break;
335                default:
336                        evaluator = DTLZ1.class;
337                        break;
338                }
339
340                bindConstant(N.class).to(n);
341                bindConstant(M.class).to(m);
342                bindConstant(Bits.class).to(bits);
343                bindProblem(creator, decoder, evaluator);
344
345        }
346
347}
